\begin{pro}\label{vl}
Let $X$ be a set, ${\cal M}\subseteq{\cal P}{^{\prime}}(X)$, ${\cal M}$ be a natural family and ${\cal O}$ be a lower-Vietoris-type topology on ${\cal M}$. Then
$\Phi:(X,{\cal T}_{{\cal O}})\longrightarrow({\cal M},{\cal O})$, where $\Phi(x)=\{x\}$ for any $x\in X$, is a homeomorphic embedding. If $(X,{\cal T}_{{\cal O}})$ is a $T_2$-space then $\Phi(X)$ is a closed subset of $({\cal M},{\cal O})$ and if, in addition, $|X|>1$ and $X\in{\cal M}$, then $\Phi(X)$ is nowhere dense in $({\cal M},{\cal O})$.
